  "texts": [
    "Suppose y ′ ∈ h p [↓x], so there is a y ⊑ x such that h p (y) = y ′.",
    "Then by ⊑-forth, y ′ = h p (y) ⊑ ′ h p (x), so y ′ ∈ h p [S] ∩ ↓ ′ h p (x).In the other direction, suppose y ′ ∈ h p [S] ∩ ↓ ′ h p (x), so there is a y ∈ S such that y ′ = h p (y) ⊑ ′ h p (x).",
    "Then by (i) above we have y ⊑ x, which with y ′ = h p (y) implies y ′ ∈ h p [↓x].",
    "This completes the proof of part 2.For part 3, assuming h is injective and y′ ∈ A ′ p, we claim that h p (h(y ′)) = y ′.",
    "As in (b) above, by definition of h p, h p (h(y ′)) = ′ {z ′ | h(y ′) ⊑ h(z ′)}, and y ′ ∈ {z ′ | h(y ′) ⊑ h(z ′)}."
